history.text: I really like movies by Martin Scorsese. He directed the Wolf of Wall Street.
I really like leonard DiCaprio as an actor.
Did you know that he produced the Wolf of Wall Street?
Yes i see that he has Directed The Wolf of Wall Street.
Apparently The Wolf of Wall Street is considered a black comedy. Jonah Hill is usually funny and he was in it.
I believe this is a good movie. I don't believe the critical responses that are given.
You would think that with so many big name actors that it would have scored higher.
I know it is a shame that movies can me made or broken just with a few bad views by critics.
One critic wrote "made duller by their delusions of being interesting because they are high"... wasn't that the idea behind Fast Times at Ridgemont High?
I think this movie has a really good plot to it.
The critics called it narrow in scope.
It is also trying to say that we are only interested in characters who are dull people to start with.
Mattew Mcconaughey is not a dull actor

I would like to be dull and have all that money.
Funny how he makes so much money selling penny stocks.
They even say that the basic method of this firm is a pump and dump scam.
Apparently you get to buy lots of prostitutes if you are a rich scam artist working n the stock market.
Sounds like it is getting more interesting when the wife finds out and then he goes out and marries again.
He makes $22 million in three hours. That is impressive.
Very impressive indeed.
It also gets the attention of the FBI and that is not always good.
So basically this guy hires a bunch of crooks to pose as stock brokers and scam a bunch of people. And then he makes a big deal for $22 million. And then he needs to run from the law.
Then Saurel gets arrested in florida and turns evidence on Jordan that gets him arrested by the FBI.
Three years minimum security prison? That's it for $22 million? Holy cow!
Now Naomi is divorcing Jordan for all of this now.
She is then going to take full custody of their children.
Yeah, well that makes sense. You would think that some of that money would be "stashed away" somewhere though wouldn't you?
I mean, after all those drugs and stuff the kids shouldn't be part of that.
After Jordan turns evidence and is release he will now have to make a living hosting seminars on a sales technique.
How do you think he crashed in his own driveway? That had to have been hysterical?
I would have left him also those kids are innocent through all of this.
